    public class MaxSizeConcurrentHashSet<E>
extends Object
implements Set<E>, Serializable
    A hash set supporting full concurrency of retrievals and high expected concurrency for updates but with an (adjustable) maximum size. The maximum only prevents further add operations. It doesn't stop the maximum being exceeded when first loaded or via an addAll(). This is deliberate!
